%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20engineer%2C%20says%20the%20nature%20of%20her%20work%20is%20changing%20because%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEach%20week%20she%20spends%20one%20to%20two%20hours%20upskilling%20on%20new%20AI%20tools%20for%20her%20role.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGiven%20the%20pace%20of%20advancement%2C%20Patnaik%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20naturally%20interests%20her.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Pratiksha%20Patnaik%2C%20a%2030-year-old%20cloud%20infrastructure%20engineer%20at%20Google%20Cloud%20Consulting%2C%20based%20in%20Seattle.%20Her%20identity%20and%20employment%20have%20been%20verified%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20with%20Google%20for%20around%20three%20years%20and%20I%20started%20as%20an%20infrastructure%20engineer.%20I'm%20still%20an%20infrastructure%20engineer%20and%20on%20a%20day-to-day%20basis%2C%20I%20work%20with%20customers%20to%20build%20different%20solutions%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20customer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20was%20mostly%20involved%20with%20networking%20security%20and%20infrastructure%20customers.%20But%20as%20we%20saw%20the%20AI%20wave%20come%20in%2C%20we%20started%20focusing%20more%20on%20customers%20that%20want%20to%20adopt%20gen%20AI%20products%20and%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgooglers-share-transition-to-ai-roles-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etransition%20into%20an%20AI%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I'm%20working%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20AI%20services%2C%20and%20AI%20engineers%20who%20are%20working%20on%20features%20for%20those%20services.%20My%20job%20is%20a%20combination%20of%20working%20with%20customers%20and%20the%20product%20team%2C%20to%20provide%20technical%20solutions%20for%20customers.%20It's%20a%20constant%20feedback%20loop%20to%20figure%20out%20if%20the%20solution%20we're%20building%20is%20right%20for%20the%20customer%20we're%20working%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20job%20is%20to%20know%20how%20these%20products%20work.%20Sometimes%20when%20we%20work%20on%20the%20products%2C%20we%20identify%20feature%20gaps%20or%20bugs%2C%20so%20we%20need%20to%20work%20with%20the%20product%20team%20or%20engineering%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20in%20the%20same%20role%20the%20whole%20time%2C%20but%20the%20nature%20of%20my%20job%20is%20changing%20because%20of%20everything%20going%20on%20in%20the%20AI%20space.%20We%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20demand%20in%20AI%20products%20and%20we%20have%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20trainings%20on%20it%20to%20deliver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225970d54b-344a-4109-a24d-3f5445c86046%5C%22%3EI%20spend%20an%20hour%20or%20two%20weekly%20on%20trainings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20AI%20progresses%2C%20the%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-fatigue-burnout-software-engineer-essay-siddhant-khare-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edifficult%20it's%20become%20to%20keep%20up%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20the%20rate%20of%20AI%20innovation%20gets%20quicker%2C%20the%20role%20of%20engineers%20has%20transitioned%20from%20mastery%20to%20continuous%20adaptation%20at%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20being%20aware%20of%20everything%20that's%20happening%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20along%20with%20what%20we%20have%20to%20do%20with%20the%20customer%2C%20has%20changed%20dramatically%20from%20what%20it%20was%20like%20a%20year%20ago.%20Back%20then%2C%20we%20had%20to%20execute%20within%20known%20constraints.%20But%20as%20time%20passes%20and%20AI%20evolves%20rapidly%2C%20those%20perimeters%20have%20dissolved%20and%20we%20have%20to%20invest%20much%20more%20time%20to%20learning%20about%20changes%20in%20this%20space.%20We%20now%20have%20to%20navigate%20an%20ever-expanding%20problem%20space%20alongside%20our%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spend%20around%20one%20to%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-engineer-said-landing-ai-role-took-year-daily-upskilling-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehours%20a%20week%20up-skilling%20on%20new%20concepts%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20internal%20trainings%20that%20we%20can%20utilize.%20So%20I%20see%20if%20there%20is%20something%20new%20that%20I'm%20interested%20in%20learning%20about%20and%20that%20can%20help%20me%20do%20my%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20gaining%20a%20deeper%20level%20of%20understanding%20in%20high-performance%20computing%2C%20AI%20observability%2C%20model%20performance%20benchmarking%2C%20and%20the%20underlying%20architecture%20of%20GPUs%20and%20TPUs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d5649c48-81fb-4dcc-a4c5-2ea743c14a7b%5C%22%3EIt%20can%20get%20overwhelming%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employee-ai-adoption-non-technical-software-engineer-performance-review-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eculture%20at%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20very%20much%20about%20constantly%20learning.%20Every%20day%20we%20learn%20about%20a%20new%20tool%20or%20model%20version.%20That%20motivates%20me%20to%20keep%20learning.%20We%20also%20have%20to%20skill%20up%20in%20order%20to%20put%20our%20best%20foot%20forward%20in%20front%20of%20the%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20the%20pace%20of%20technology%20nowadays%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20need%20to%20know%20everything%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20I%20don't%20learn%2C%20I%20might%20be%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%20that%20it's%20not%20practically%20possible%20to%20know%20everything%20with%20the%20changes%20that%20are%20coming%20out%20at%20an%20exponential%20rate.%20To%20remain%20effective%20without%20burning%20out%2C%20I%20prioritize%20intentional%20depth%20over%20exhaustive%20consumption.%20By%20focusing%20on%20what%20really%20interests%20me%2C%20I%20can%20make%20sure%20that%20my%20learning%20is%20not%20just%20a%20chore%20of%20%26quot%3Bkeeping%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20an%20investment%20in%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20read%20too%20much%2C%20I%20get%20overwhelmed%20and%20it's%20not%20possible%20to%20retain%20all%20of%20the%20information%20I'm%20consuming.%20We're%20at%20a%20point%20where%20the%20amount%20of%20information%20we%20have%20is%20huge%20and%20we%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20where%20to%20spend%20our%20time%20and%20what's%20the%20most%20beneficial%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20an%20engineer%20experiencing%20changes%20in%20your%20job%3F%20We'd%20love%20to%20hear%20from%20you.%20Email%20the%20reporter%20from%20a%20non-work%20device%20via%20email%20at%20aaltchek%40insider.com%20or%20secure-messaging%20platform%20Signal%20at%20aalt.19.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-google-engineer-prioritizes-learning-avoid-ai-burnout-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772535421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69601e1364858d02d21804eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-google-engineer-prioritizes-learning-avoid-ai-burnout-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pratiksha%20Patnaik%20says%20that%20it's%20not%20practical%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20every%20new%20development%2C%20and%20she%20tries%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20interests%20her%20to%20avoid%20burnout.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-google-engineer-prioritizes-learning-avoid-ai-burnout-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Madras%20HC%20bans%20illegal%20broadcast%20of%20'The%20Kerala%20Story%202'%22%2C%22content%