repayment%20overhaul%20completed%20a%20key%20phase.%3Cp%3ESAUL%20LOEB%20%2F%20AFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20public%20comment%20period%20on%20Trump's%20student-loan%20repayment%20changes%20has%20concluded.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Education%20Department%20will%20determine%20whether%20it%20will%20make%20any%20changes%20to%20its%20proposal%20before%20finalizing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20commenters%20took%20issue%20with%20the%20proposed%20caps%20on%20borrowing%20for%20advanced%20degrees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELong-awaited%20changes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-major-repayment-overhaul-big-beautiful-bill-trump-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eto%20student-loan%20repayment%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20a%20step%20closer%20to%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-repayment-overhaul-next-phase-public-comment-debt-borrowers-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epublic%20comment%20period%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20sweeping%20changes%20to%20repayment%20and%20borrowing%20concluded%20on%20Monday.%20The%20Department%20of%20Education%20will%20now%20evaluate%20the%20comments%20and%20determine%20whether%20it%20will%20change%20its%20proposed%20rule%20before%20moving%20to%20final%20implementation%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20department's%20rule%20includes%20new%20borrowing%20caps%20for%20advanced%20degrees%2C%20the%20elimination%20of%20existing%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans%2C%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20new%2C%20less%20generous%20plan%20with%20a%20longer%20timeline%20to%20debt%20relief%20and%20likely%20higher%20monthly%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20wants%20to%20hear%20about%20the%20challenges%2C%20successes%2C%20and%20unique%20experiences%20you're%20facing%20with%20your%20student%20loans.%20Do%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%3F%20Please%20fill%20out%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flnkd.in%2FeDDHUjmJ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20form%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20we'll%20be%20in%20touch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%2015%2C000%20people%20commented%20on%20the%20department's%20proposal%2C%20including%20students%2C%20advocates%2C%20and%20lawmakers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-repayment-overhaul-limits-for-nurses-public-comment-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMany%20of%20the%20comments%3C%2Fa%3E%20took%20issue%20with%20the%20department's%20proposed%20borrowing%20caps%20for%20advanced%20programs%3A%20a%20%24100%2C000%20lifetime%20limit%20for%20graduate%20students%20and%20a%20%24200%2C000%20limit%20for%20professional%20students.%20The%20department%20also%20limited%20what%20would%20qualify%20as%20%26quot%3Bprofessional%26quot%3B%20to%20a%20list%20of%2010%20programs%2C%20including%20medicine%20and%20dentistry%2C%20but%20not%20post-graduate%20nursing%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20undermine%20access%20to%20this%20education%20would%20run%20counter%20to%20this%20nation's%20stated%20goal%20of%20achieving%20the%20highest%20possible%20quality%20of%20healthcare%20for%20all%20citizens%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20public%20comment%20said.%20A%20bipartisan%20group%20of%20over%20100%20lawmakers%20wrote%20in%20a%20letter%20that%20they%20submitted%20to%20public%20comment%20that%20%26quot%3Bnow%20is%20not%20the%20time%20to%20cut%20off%20the%20student%20pipeline%20to%20these%20programs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20commenter%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BSave%20the%20SAVE%20program!!%20Allow%20us%20please%20to%20keep%20this%20affordable%20program.%26quot%3B%20Trump's%20%26quot%3Bbig%20beautiful%26quot%3B%20spending%20legislation%20called%20for%20the%20elimination%20of%20former%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20SAVE%20plan%2C%20which%20allowed%20for%20cheaper%20monthly%20payments%20and%20a%20shorter%20timeline%20to%20debt%20relief.%20The%20legislation%20would%20phase%20out%20the%20plan%20by%202028.%20While%20the%20department%20announced%20a%20proposed%20settlement%20to%20end%20the%20program%20ahead%20of%20schedule%2C%20a%20court%20declined%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-student-loan-repayment-plan-court-setback-trump-borrowers-settlement-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erule%20on%20the%20settlement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20keeping%20the%20plan%20active%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUndersecretary%20of%20Education%20Nicholas%20Kent%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20ahead%20of%20the%20public%20comment%20period%20that%20the%20repayment%20changes%20will%20ensure%20%26quot%3Bthat%20every%20professional%20in%20America%E2%80%94from%20teachers%20and%20nurses%20to%20physicians%20and%20clergy%E2%80%94can%20pursue%20their%20careers%20without%20taking%20on%20debt%20they%20may%20never%20be%20able%20to%20repay.%26quot%3B%20The%20department%20added%20in%20a%20press%20release%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bmay%20make%20changes%20to%20the%20proposed%20regulations%20in%20response%20to%20substantive%20comments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%20are%20expected%20to%20shift%20more%20federal%20borrowers%20to%20private%20lending%20to%20supplement%20the%20new%20borrowing%20caps.%20Jonathan%20Witter%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20private%20lender%20Sallie%20Mae%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-repayment-overhaul-navient-sallie-mae-excited-debt-borrowres-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eduring%20an%20earnings%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%20that%20the%20company%20is%20%26quot%3Bexcited%20about%20the%20opportunity%20created%20by%20the%20recent%20federal%20student%20lending%20reforms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-debt-repayment-overhaul-moves-to-next-step-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772532362000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a5ba1ed3e2f1aef369ce95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-debt-repayment-overhaul-moves-to-next-step-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20public%20comment%20period%20on%20Trump's%20sweeping%20changes%20to%20student-loan%20repayment%20has%20ended%2C%20bringing%20borrowers%20a%20step%20closer%20to%20finalization.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-debt-repayment-overhaul-moves-to-next-step-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20former%20MrBeast%20editor%20is%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20make%20the%20creator%20economy%20better%20for%20women%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224493%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rachel%20Kisela%2C%20video%20editor%20and%20founder%20of%20EditHers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f68e41fb3fcb4264876ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222996%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERachel%20Kisela%2C%20a%20former%20MrBeast%20video%20editor%2C%20started%20EditHers%20to%20help%20more%20women%20like%20her%20find%20creator%20economy%20work.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20credit%3A%20Karan%20Singh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFormer%20MrBeast%20editor%20Rachel%20Kisela%20started%20a%20Discord%20called%20EditHers%20to%20help%20fellow%20women%20editors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20creator%20economy%20is%20booming%2C%20but%20job%20seekers%20face%20challenges.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEditHers%20is%20part%20job%20board%2C%20part%20guild%2C%20part%20therapy%20group%2C%20and%20part%20skill%20incubator.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcreator-platforms-make-more-money-old-media-wpp-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecreator%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20growing%20fast%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20opportunities%20aren't%20being%20shared%20equally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERachel%20Kisela%2C%20a%20freelance%20video%20editor%20from%20Seattle%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmrbeast%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMrBeast%3C%2Fa%3E%20alum%2C%20noticed%20she%20was%20an%20anomaly%20as%20a%20woman%20in%20the%20field.%20That%20perception%20was%20confirmed%20by%20data%20she%20saw%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zippia.com%2Fvideo-editor-jobs%2Fdemographics%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecareer%20site%20Zippia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20showed%20that%2076%25%20of%20video%20editors%20are%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20creators%20began%20asking%20Kisela%20for%20recommendations%20for%20other%20female%20editors%2C%20she%20got%20an%20idea.%20In%202024%2C%20Kisela%2C%2027%2C%20launched%20EditHers%2C%20a%20Discord%20community%20to%20match%20female%20editors%20with%20hirers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20community%20has%20grown%20to%20nearly%20200%20editors%20and%20around%20100%20creators%2C%20including%20top%20players%20like%20Airrack%20and%20Smosh%2C%20as%20well%20as%20her%20former%20employer%2C%20where%20she%20was%20a%20lead%20video%20editor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-ceos-behind-youtubes-biggest-stars-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etop%20YouTube%20creators%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20subscriber%20count%20are%20overwhelmingly%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20can%20be%20kind%20of%20bro-y%2C%26quot%3B%20Kisela%20said%20of%20YouTube.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEditing%20is%20also%20technical%20work%2C%20and%20Kisela%20said%20she'd%20observed%20that%20it%20tended%20to%20draw%20more%20men%20than%20women.%20She%20said%20she's%20had%20people%20assume%20she%20doesn't%20know%20how%20to%20use%20Adobe%20Premiere%2C%20the%20industry's%20standard%20editing%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20started%20this%20community%20because%20there%20was%20no%20space%20like%20this%2C%20and%20to%20my%20knowledge%2C%20there%20still%20is%20no%20other%20space%20like%20this%20on%20the%20internet%20for%20women%20YouTube%20editors%20to%20talk%20about%20their%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20Kisela%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223683b5ac-516c-45c9-8576-ed0ad0b672f1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEditHers%20is%20part%20job%20board%2C%20part%20therapy%20group%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEditHers%2C%20for%20now%20a%20passion%20project%20that%20Kisela%20manages%20in%20addition%20to%20her%20paid%20freelance%20work%2C%20is%20part%20job%20board%2C%20part%20guild%2C%20part%20therapy%20group%2C%20and%20part%20skill%20incubator.%20It's%20become%20a%20place%20where%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhollywood-tv-movie-learn-about-creators-at-industry-master-class-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20opportunities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20participants%20trade%20tips%20about%20pay%20and%20skills%20and%20share%20openly%20about%20sexism%20they've%20encountered.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKisela%20said%20building%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcreator-income-inequality-grows-top-earners-paydays-rise-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecareer%20in%20the%20creator%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20started%20out%20cold%20emailing%20hundreds%20of%20creators%20when%20I%20was%20in%20college%20and%20just%20offering%20to%20help%20them%20out%2C%20build%20a%20YouTube%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20jobs%20you%20don't%20get%20by%20just%20applying%2C%20but%20just%20by%20intercepting%20the%20right%20creator%20at%20the%20right%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETyler%20Allen%2C%20manager%20of%20the%20YouTube%20creator%20HopeScope%2C%20said%20EditHers%20has%20helped%20fill%20a%20need%20on%20the%20hiring%20end.%20HopeScope%20sponsored%20a%20panel%20discussion%20that%20Kisela%20put%20on%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20in%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20just%20aren't%20as%20many%20women%20editors%20as%20male%20editors%2C%26quot%3B%20Allen%20said.%20%26quot%3BEditors%20are%20hard%20to%20find%20on%20the%20internet.%20If%20I'm%20looking%20for%20a%20video%20editor%2C%20they%20probably%20don't%20have%20a%20LinkedIn.%20When%20I%20have%20four%20job%20listings%2C%20I%20would%20say%2090%2B%25%20that%20apply%20are%20men.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPay%20is%20always%20a%20big%20topic%20on%20EditHers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20do%20I%20raise%20my%20rates%20over%20time%3F%20I've%20been%20working%20with%20one%20creator%20for%20several%20years%2C%20and%20I%20want%20to%20raise%20my%20rates%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20sure%20how%20to%20have%20that%20discussion%2C%26quot%3B%20Kisela%20said%2C%20ticking%20off%20common%20questions.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20one%20standardized%20way%20to%20charge%20clients%20for%20video%20editing%20in%20the%20YouTube%20space.%20Very%20tight%20deadlines%2C%20insane%20hours.%20A%20lot%20of%20these%20companies%20don't%20have%20the%20benefits%20of%20a%20traditional%20job%2C%20health%20insurance%2C%20stuff%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJillian%20Diblasio%2C%20a%20freelance%20editor%20and%20early%20member%20of%20EditHers%2C%20said%20the%20community%20had%20helped%20her%20not%20only%20find%20jobs%20but%20also%20learn%20what%20to%20charge%20and%20what's%20expected%20in%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20helps%20women%20empower%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20safe%20space%20where%20we%20can%20ask%20questions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22abb8b84d-e7bf-4b91-8d2b-bd3323f0cbe7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKisela's%20takeaways%20from%20MrBeast%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKisela%20left%20North%20Carolina-based%20MrBeast%20in%202023%20to%20return%20to%20the%20West%20Coast%20and%20have%20the%20freedom%20that%20freelancing%20affords.%20(In%20addition%20to%20EditHers%2C%20she%20runs%20an%20Etsy%20shop%20selling%20disco%20balls%20and%20plans%20to%20be%20a%20digital%20nomad.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKisela%20said%20she%20was%20impressed%20by%20the%20mission-driven%20content%2C%20an%20element%20of%20MrBeast's%20programming%2C%20and%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmrbeast-how-production-team-makes-youtube-videos-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efounder%20Jimmy%20Donaldson%3C%2Fa%3E's%20well-documented%20attention%20to%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20cited%20one%20video%20she%20worked%20on%20where%20MrBeast%20said%20he%20paid%20for%20cataract%20surgery%20to%20cure%201%2C000%20people's%20blindness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20stuff%20is%20real%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20brought%20me%20a%20lot%20of%20purpose%20when%20I%20was%20working%20there%2C%20just%20knowing%20that%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20in%20his%20position%20would%20not%20be%20doing%20that%20type%20of%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20self-described%20workaholic%2C%20Kisela%20is%20aware%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhannah-witton-youtube-clinic-support-creators-facing-burnout-is-open-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epotential%20for%20burnout%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20comes%20with%20gig%20work.%20Her%20answer%20is%20to%20try%20to%20make%20money%20in%20as%20many%20ways%20as%20she%20can%2C%20such%20as%20consulting%20and%20her%20Etsy%20work.%20This%20helps%20diversify%20the%20type%20of%20work%20she%20does%20and%20limits%20her%20screen%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKisela%20said%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20in%20her%20generation%20are%20working%20in%20the%20gig%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20try%20to%20embrace%20that%20and%20find%20as%20many%20ways%20to%20make%20money%20as%20I%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20keeps%20my%20editing%20fun%20because%20I'm%20not%20editing%2080%20hours%20a%20week.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-mrbeast-editor-built-site-to-tackle-creator-gender-gap-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772532361000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f68f4e8408f667180463f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-mrbeast-editor-built-site-to-tackle-creator-gender-gap-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rachel%20Kisela%20saw%20a%20gender%20gap%20among%20YouTube%20editors%2C%20so%20she%20built%20a%20site%20to%20connect%20women%20editors%20and%20employers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmoses%40insider.com%20(Lucia%20Moses)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-mrbeast-editor-built-site-to-tackle-creator-gender-gap-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20compatibility%20researcher%20says%20dating%20apps%20are%20'mostly%20a%20waste%20of%20time.'%20Here's%20how%20to%20find%20a%20partner%20you%20actually%20click%20with.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224538%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20canoodling%20outside%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a5be00d3e2f1aef369cf23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223404%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMost%20couples%20don't%20feel%20a%20%26quot%3Bspark%26quot%3B%20the%20first%20time%20they%20meet%20their%20partner.%3Cp%3EJanina%20Steinmetz%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20psychology%20researcher%20said%20dating%20apps%20are%20mostly%20unhelpful%20for%20finding%20a%20compatible%20partner.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20couples%20build%20compatibility%2C%20rather%20than%20automatically%20being%20perfect%20fits%20for%20each%20other.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDating%20apps%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20reject%20people%20quickly%20and%20label%20benign%20behaviors%20as%20red%20flags.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EToday's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-dating-apps-tinder-hinge-bumble-alternatives-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edating%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20marketed%20to%20help%20you%20find%20a%20compatible%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20psychology%20researcher%2C%20it's%20practically%20useless%20for%20actually%20finding%20one%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20similar%20your%20interests%2C%20lifestyles%2C%20or%20political%20views%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20mostly%20a%20waste%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Paul%20Eastwick%2C%20a%20psychology%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Davis%2C%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BBonded%20by%20Evolution%3A%20The%20New%20Science%20of%20Love%20and%20Connection%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20can%20feel%20productive%20to%20filter%20out%20prospective%20partners%2C%20Eastwick%20said%20attraction%20is%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20to%20be%20more%20or%20less%20a%20dart%20throw%26quot%3B%20when%20you%20actually%20meet%20the%20person%20on%20the%20other%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20because%20many%20of%20us%20look%20at%20compatibility%20the%20wrong%20way%2C%20he%20said%2C%20focusing%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-tell-if-someone-is-right-for-you-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebroad%20personality%20traits%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20%26quot%3Badventurous%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bfunny.%26quot%3B%20That%20thinking%20often%20leads%20us%20astray%20because%20there's%20no%20way%20to%20know%20whether%20the%20person%2C%20with%20our%20laundry%20list%20of%20dream%20qualities%2C%20will%20actually%20make%20us%20feel%20supported%20in%20the%20way%20we%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompatibility%20is%20a%20construction%20process%20rather%20than%20an%20initial%20attraction%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Eastwick%20said.%20Rather%20than%20falling%20into%20relationships%20that%20fit%20us%20perfectly%2C%20the%20happiest%20couples%20find%20someone%20they%20really%20like%2C%20focus%20on%20their%20similarities%2C%20and%20build%20a%20compatible%20relationship%20over%20time.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20very%20complicated%20thing%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20compatibility%20isn't%20straightforward%2C%20finding%20someone%20who%20clicks%20with%20you%20is%20less%20daunting%20than%20it%20sounds.%20Eastwick%20shared%20three%20tips%20for%20finding%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-of-strong-marriage-couples-therapist-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong-term%20partner%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20none%20of%20which%20involve%20swiping%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227d1536d6-0922-4f6a-b705-cf617f02a414%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20you're%20on%20the%20fence%2C%20commit%20to%20three%20dates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225514%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20at%20pub%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a5bd981fb3fcb42648bcd2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224136%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMost%20couples%20don't%20feel%20a%20%26quot%3Bspark%26quot%3B%20the%20first%20time%20they%20meet%20their%20partner.%3Cp%3EIppei%20Naoi%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20dating%20apps%2C%20one%20of%20Eastwick's%20biggest%20concerns%20is%20the%20illusion%20of%20endless%20matches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20have%20so%20many%20options%2C%20it%20means%20that%20you%20don't%20give%20those%20options%20much%20of%20a%20shot%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20puts%20the%20onus%20on%20people%20to%20wow%20each%20other%2020%20minutes%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-rejected-generation-college-careers-jobs-dating-ghosting-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecoffee%20date%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20a%20second%20date%2C%20to%20everyone's%20detriment.%20%26quot%3BOur%20opinions%20of%20somebody%20will%20get%20more%20and%20more%20variable%20as%20we%20get%20to%20know%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStatistically%2C%20the%20chances%20that%20you'll%20feel%20an%20immediate%20spark%20on%20that%20first%20date%20are%20slim.%20According%20to%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic1.squarespace.com%2Fstatic%2F504114b1e4b0b97fe5a520af%2Ft%2F5b06f983575d1fdad114fc63%2F1527183756161%2FEastwickKeneskiMorganMcDonaldHuang2018JEPG.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eown%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Eastwick%20said%20most%20people%20in%20long-term%20relationships%20felt%20%26quot%3Bmiddling%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20first%20impressions%20of%20their%20partners.%20Rather%20than%20feeling%20lightning%20bolts%2C%20most%20people%20took%20time%20to%20build%20attraction%20for%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20find%20the%20perfect%20match%2C%20according%20to%20a%20psychology%20researcher%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJoin%20hobby%20groups%20and%20clubs%20to%20slowly%20get%20to%20know%20new%20people%20without%20pressure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGo%20on%20at%20least%203%20dates%20before%20deciding%20how%20you%20feel%20about%20the%20other%20person.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFocus%20on%20how%20good%20someone%20makes%20you%20feel%20rather%20than%20red%20flags.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhere%20you%20start%20doesn't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20predictive%20power%20over%20where%20this%20thing%20is%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20these%20relationships%20eventually%20get%20to%20the%20same%20highs%20of%2C%20'I%20fell%20for%20this%20person.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Eastwick%20advocates%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-third-date-brought-us-closer-still-together-hiking-challenge-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree-date%20rule%3A%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20you%20generally%20like%20someone%20but%20don't%20know%20if%20you%20feel%20something%20just%20yet.%20He%20explained%2C%20%26quot%3BYour%20impression's%20going%20to%20be%20kind%20of%20unstable%20for%20those%20first%20two%20dates%2C%20but%20at%20least%20you%20reach%20some%20stability%20after%20a%20third.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220c290f59-27c8-4123-9585-53122a9db8fb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoin%20groups%20for%20slow-burn%20connections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224206%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20hiking%20in%20forest%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a5b93ed3e2f1aef369ce6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223154%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECouples%20build%20compatibility%20over%20time%2C%20rather%20than%20click%20into%20relationships%20together%2C%20Dr.%20Paul%20Eastwick%2C%20a%20psychology%20researcher%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3Cp%3EDrazen%20Zigic%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHumans%20evolved%20in%20small%20groups%2C%20Eastwick%20said.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20dating%2C%20we%20should%20strive%20to%20emulate%20that%20environment%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20groups%20interacting%20over%20long%20stretches%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20such%20as%20co-ed%20sports%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frun-club-making-friends-dating-app-alternatives-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erun%20clubs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dance%20classes%2C%20and%20improv%20workshops.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20people%20to%20get%20together%20with%20the%20same%20people%20on%20repeated%20occasions%20without%20the%20ability%20to%20opt%20out%20if%20they%20don't%20initially%20blow%20you%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20complicating%20factor%3A%20single%20straight%20men%20need%20to%20start%20showing%20up%20more.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2026%2F02%2F22%2Fpodcasts%2Fthe-daily%2Fis-the-swipe-era-over.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20episode%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20The%20Daily%20revealed%20that%20at%20a%20recent%20in-person%20dating%20event%2C%20three%20times%20as%20many%20women%20showed%20up%20as%20did%20men%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20women%20paid%20%24100%20to%20attend%20while%20men%20went%20for%20free.%20Across%20the%20board%2C%20many%20straight%20women%20feel%20like%20they're%20consistently%20putting%20themselves%20out%20there%2C%20only%20to%20find%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-winners-loneliness-epidemic-nice-guys-with-jobs-dating-apps-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efew%20(if%20any)%20men%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20talk%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20echoes%20a%20trend%20Eastwick%20noticed%20himself%20at%20events%20promoting%20his%20book.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20either%20women%20or%20couples.%20Where%20are%20the%20gaggles%20of%20men%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20may%20be%20that%20it's%20men%20who%20need%20this%20particular%20advice%20more%20than%20women%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22011f4319-cfe2-4945-b9ab-30e4200e3f21%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECount%20the%20green%20flags%2C%20not%20the%20red%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224653%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20kissing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a5bc781fb3fcb42648bcab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223490%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFocusing%20on%20green%20flags%20gets%20you%20out%20of%20the%20habit%20of%20overanalyzing%20a%20relationship.%3Cp%3EJanina%20Steinmetz%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEastwick%20said%20there%20are%20two%20types%20of%20red%20flags%20people%20look%20for%20in%20potential%20partners%20%E2%80%94%20and%20one%20of%20them%20might%20be%20sabotaging%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20kind%20is%20anything%20that%20gives%20you%20an%20immediate%20%26quot%3Bick%2C%26quot%3B%20like%20a%20date%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-date-red-flags-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebeing%20rude%20to%20waitstaff%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20droning%20on%20the%20whole%20time%20without%20asking%20you%20a%20single%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20is%20more%20about%20trying%20to%20predict%20future%20heartbreak.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20person%20not%20texting%20you%20back%20at%20the%20cadence%20you'd%20like.%20You%20might%20%26quot%3Bforecast%26quot%3B%20that%20this%20is%20an%20insurmountable%20problem%20and%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20person's%20ultimate%20flakiness%20and%20carelessness%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20difference%20you%20can%20work%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20we've%20internalized%20all%20this%20noise%20out%20here%2C%20and%20it's%20become%20this%20little%20voice%20in%20our%20head%20that%20urges%20caution%20and%20building%20walls%2C%26quot%3B%20Eastwick%20said.%20%26quot%3BRelationships%20don't%20work%20if%20people%20do%20that.%20It's%20antithetical%3A%20You%20have%20to%20be%20vulnerable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20trouble%20getting%20out%20of%20analytical%20mode%2C%20he%20encourages%20shifting%20to%20a%20more%20positive%20frame%20of%20mind.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20people%20to%20count%20green%20flags%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdating-app-fatigue-setting-up-friends-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edating%20environment%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20we're%20constantly%20scouring%20profiles%20and%20social%20media%20posts%2C%20the%20best%20remedy%20is%20to%20simply%20focus%20on%20how%20you%20feel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-find-compatible-partner-dating-app-fatigue-researcher-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772532241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a5bcbf1fb3fcb42648bcb7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-find-compatible-partner-dating-app-fatigue-researcher-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20psychology%20researcher%20shared%20why%20dating%20apps%20aren't%20helpful%20for%20finding%20compatibility%2C%20and%20how%20to%20find%20a%20great%20match%20instead.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpugachevsky%40businessinsider.com%20(Julia%20Pugachevsky)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-find-compatible-partner-dating-app-fatigue-researcher-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22He%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20colon%20cancer%20at%2031%20in%20prison%2C%20and%20his%20survival%20odds%20weren't%20great.%20Now%2059%2C%20he%20says%20spiraling%20is%20pointless.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Nick%20Leeson%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a1d7101fb3fcb426489bf5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENick%20Leeson%20was%20given%20a%2060%25%20chance%20of%20living%20within%20five%20years%20after%20his%20diagnosis.%20That%20was%2028%20years%20ago.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Nick%20Leeson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENick%20Leeson's%20unauthorized%20trades%20led%20to%20Barings%20Bank's%20collapse%2C%20a%20major%20banking%20scandal%20in%201995.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELeeson%20battled%20colon%20cancer%20during%20his%20imprisonment%2C%20undergoing%20surgery%20and%20chemotherapy%20treatment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPost-cancer%2C%20Leeson%20emphasizes%20that%20mindset%20and%20regular%20checkups%20are%20key%20to%20a%20full%20life%20post-cancer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201995%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-billion-dollar-bank-fraud-actually-works-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENick%20Leeson%3C%2Fa%3E%20became%20synonymous%20with%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20banking%20collapses%20in%20British%20history.%20His%20unauthorized%20trades%20resulted%20in%20over%20a%20billion%20dollars%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapi.parliament.uk%2Fhistoric-hansard%2Flords%2F1995%2Fjul%2F18%2Fbarings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E827%20million%20pounds%3C%2Fa%3E)%20in%20losses%20and%20brought%20down%20Barings%20Bank%2C%20a%20233-year-old%20merchant%20bank.%20The%20fallout%20led%20to%20his%20arrest%2C%20extradition%2C%20and%20imprisonment%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20unfolded%20during%20his%20sentence%20drew%20less%20public%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20serving%20time%20at%20Tanah%20Merah%20prison%2C%20Leeson%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-so-many-young-people-getting-colon-cancer-answer-infancy-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ediagnosed%20with%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20symptoms%20began%20with%20dizziness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20the%20tumor%20in%20his%20colon%20grew%20so%20large%20that%20it%20collapsed%20one%20of%20his%20lungs%2C%20and%20he%20underwent%20immediate%20surgery%20in%201998.%20The%20doctors%20removed%20a%20mass%20nearly%20the%20size%20of%20a%20softball.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20given%20a%2060%25%20chance%20of%20living%20for%20five%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Leeson%20was%20released%20from%20prison%20in%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22How%20Bank%20Fraud%20Actually%20Works%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FauTgzqrz-puACk8ZV.html%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%2030%20years%20later%2C%20Leeson%20has%20undergone%20at%20least%2010%20colonoscopies%20since%20the%20surgery%20as%20preventive%20follow-ups.%20He's%20had%20no%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexercise-can-prevent-recurrent-colon-cancer-study-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecurrence%20of%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20says%20that%20living%20a%20full%20life%20after%20cancer%20is%20about%20having%20the%20right%20mindset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20become%20very%20aware%20that%20there%20are%20things%20in%20your%20life%20you%20can%20influence%20and%20things%20in%20your%20life%20that%20you%20can't%20influence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20diagnosed%2C%20you%20can't%20influence%20the%20fact%20that%20you've%20been%20diagnosed%20and%20that%20you%20have%20it.%20What%20you%20can%20influence%20is%20how%20you%20move%20forward%20from%20that%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d8a8416-b1ce-4663-9559-9b4257b0dd0f%5C%22%3EThe%20biggest%20warning%20sign%20he%20ignored%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221451%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nick%20Leeson%20at%20Singapore%20airpot%20in%20the%20'90s%20surrounded%20by%20police%20officers.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a1d99cd3e2f1aef369af1b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22981%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENick%20Leeson%20at%20Singapore's%20Changi%20airport%20surrounded%20by%20local%20police%20officers%20after%20his%20extradition%20from%20Germany.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Macdougall%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20prison%2C%20Leeson's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-misdiagnosis-young-people-ibs-gluten-allergy-symptoms-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eearly%20symptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%20didn't%20immediately%20register%20as%20something%20serious.%20He%20says%20that%20he%20would%20lie%20on%20the%20floor%20most%20of%20the%20day%20and%20when%20he%20stood%20up%2C%20%26quot%3BI'd%20get%20very%20dizzy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%2030%20when%20the%20dizzy%20spells%20started.%20Looking%20back%20now%2C%20he%20says%20it%20was%20a%20sign%20that%20something%20was%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20shouldn't%20happen%20to%20anybody%20at%20that%20sort%20of%20age%2C%20so%20that%20was%20probably%20the%20biggest%20warning%20sign%20that%20I%20was%20ignoring%20at%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20later%20experienced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frectal-bleeding-most-common-early-sign-of-colon-cancer-taboo-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echanges%20in%20his%20stool%20patterns%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20sharp%2C%20stabbing%20stomach%20pain%20before%20losing%20consciousness%20after%20his%20lung%20collapsed%2C%20and%20he%20was%20taken%20for%20surgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20still%20incarcerated%2C%20Leeson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-true-hidden-cost-price-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eunderwent%20chemotherapy%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20five%20days%20on%2C%20followed%20by%20three%20weeks%20off%2C%20for%20six%20months.%20What%20helped%20him%20get%20through%20it%20were%20two%20books%20a%20friend%20sent%20him%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20You%20Need%20to%20Know%20About%20Cancer%20of%20the%20Colon%20and%20Rectum%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BChicken%20Soup%20for%20the%20Surviving%20Soul.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20them%20aren't%20the%20most%20encouraging%20stories%2C%26quot%3B%20Leeson%20said%20of%20%26quot%3BChick%20Soup.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BWhile%20it's%20difficult%20to%20read%2C%20whilst%20you're%20experiencing%20some%20of%20these%20things%20yourself%2C%20it%20does%20have%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20uplift%2C%20and%20for%20me%20it%20had%20a%20positive%20message.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c78eacdf-0a0d-4a37-b82e-599eb8c48946%5C%22%3ELiving%20a%20full%20life%20after%20cancer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nick%20Leeson%20on%20Big%20Brother%20stage%20in%20the%20UK.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a1dad61fb3fcb426489caa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222423%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENick%20Leeson%20was%20a%20contestant%20on%20Celebrity%20Big%20Brother%20UK%20in%202018.%20He%20placed%20fourth.%3Cp%3EStuart%20C.%20Wilson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELeeson%20says%20colon%20cancer%20did%20not%20fundamentally%20change%20his%20outlook%20on%20life.%20Rather%2C%20it%20reinforced%20how%20he%20approaches%20setbacks.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20happened%2C%20right%3F%20There's%20no%20point%20of%20getting%20into%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-ceo-with-colon-cancer-leadership-lessons-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Espiral%20of%20self-pity%20or%20depression%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20negativity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20self-pity%20has%20its%20place%2C%20but%20only%20briefly.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20feel%20sorry%20for%20yourself%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20there's%20any%20issue%20with%20that%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20really%20push%20you%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20less%20that%20you%20can%20wallow%20in%20the%20grief%2C%20in%20the%20self-pity%2C%20the%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20stresses%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-dismissed-doctors-years-diagnosed-stage-3-colon-cancer-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eproactive%20with%20medical%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20diagnosing%20yourself%20online.%20Instead%2C%20he%20maintains%20an%20open%20line%20of%20communication%20with%20his%20specialist%20and%20gets%20regular%20checkups.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I'm%20worried%20about%20something%2C%20I%20phone%20him.%20I%20don't%20Google%20and%20try%20to%20work%20out%20what's%20going%20on.%20I%20think%20that%20can%20be%20dangerous%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Leeson%20hasn't%20radically%20changed%20his%20lifestyle.%20%26quot%3BI%20eat%20as%20badly%20as%20I%20did%2030%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20oncologist%20said%20to%20me%20I%20shouldn't%20be%20eating%20so%20much%20red%20meat%2C%20ice%20cream%2C%20and%20cake.%20I%20eat%20all%20of%20them%20in%20abundance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-doctors-give-diet-advice-best-and-worst-foods-for-cancer-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDoctors%20who%20treat%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it's%20best%20to%20avoid%20sugary%20drinks%2C%20red%20and%20other%20processed%20meats%2C%20and%20drinking%20alcohol%20heavily.%20Moreover%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvegan-diets-increased-colon-cancer-risk-study-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20pescatarians%20had%20a%20lower%20risk%20of%20colorectal%20cancer%20compared%20to%20red%20meat%20eaters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeeson%20balances%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctor-studies-gut-health-colon-cancer-lowers-his-risk-prevent-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ediet%20with%20exercise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20attending%20strength%20and%20conditioning%20classes%20three%20to%20four%20times%20a%20week%20and%20spinning%20occasionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20get%20yourself%20back%20to%20a%20situation%20where%20you're%20still%20exercising%2C%20you're%20still%20getting%20out%20and%20about%2C%20and%20you're%20enjoying%20your%20life%20as%20you%20used%20to%20before%2C%20I%20think%20psychologically%20that%20makes%20everything%20a%20lot%20easier%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%